<section id="how-it-works" class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title">Two copy-pastes. That's it.</h2>
    <p class="section-subtitle">Add the MCP snippet. Paste the behavioural prompt. Done.</p>
    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step">
        <h3>Connect</h3>
        <p>Add the MCP server to your AI client's config. Covalence generates the snippet for you.</p>
        <div class="code-block">
          <div class="code-header">
            <span>Claude Desktop — config.json</span>
          </div>
          <pre><code>{`{
  "mcpServers": {
    "covalence": {
      "command": "/Applications/Covalence.app/Contents/MacOS/cov-mcp"
    }
  }
}`}</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="step">
        <h3>Instruct</h3>
        <p>Paste the behavioral prompt so your AI knows when to store and search memories.</p>
        <div class="code-block">
          <div class="code-header">
            <span>Claude Desktop — Project instructions</span>
          </div>
          <pre class="wrap"><code>{`You have access to Covalence, a persistent
memory layer. Search memory at the start
of conversations. Store important decisions,
context, and preferences. Use retrieved
context naturally …`}</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

